createGAFillerGroup(25.10)                          createGAFillerGroup(25.10)

Name
       createGAFillerGroup - It creates gate array filler groups for the post-
       mask ecoPlace flow

Syntax
       createGAFillerGroup

       [-help]

       -ga_cells <gaCellList>

       -ga_fillers <gaFillerCellList >

       -group <groupName>

       It  creates  gate  array filler groups for the post-mask ecoPlace flow.
       When   a    filler    group    is    created,    ecoPlace    -place_de-
       tail_use_GA_filler_groups  true  can  only place the GA cells at the GA
       filler location that is included in the same filler group.

       This command can be used multiple times to define  several  gate  array
       groups  for  ecoPlace.  If one filler group name is defined many times,
       the last one will be kept.

Parameters
       -ga_cells <gaCellList>
              Specifies the list of GA cells. The * wildcard is  supported  to
              specify the cell list.

       -ga_fillers <gaFillerCellList>
              Specifies the list of GA filler cells.

              Note:  One  GA  cell  or GA filler cell cannot be defined in two
              groups, otherwise it will give error.

       -group <groupName>
              Specifies the group name.

Example
       The following commands show the flow for GA Filler groups:

       innovus>  createGAFillerGroup  -ga_cells   <GA_cell_list>   -ga_fillers
       <GA_filler_list> -group <group>

       innovus> ecoPlace -place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups true

